5th ODI, Vadodara, Oct 11 2007, Australia tour of India

India

148

Australia

(25.5/50 ov)149/1
Australia won by 9 wickets (with 145 balls remaining)
Player Of The Match
Mitchell Johnson, AUS
5/26
Summary
Scorecard
Report
Commentary
Statistics
Overs
News
Photos

India won the toss but combusted on a difficult pitch. Brett Lee and Mitchell Johnson bowled well to nail early wickets from which India never recovered. Sachin Tendulkar and Irfan Pathan added 49 but that stand was snapped at a crucial time. Then the last two men put on 41 to get India up to 148 but theres no hiding the fact India didnt bat out even 40 overs. Australia need 149 to ensure they cant lose the series. Stay with us for their chase shortly.

8.30 am local Hello and a very warm welcome to Cricinfo's live coverage of the fifth ODI between India and Australia at Vadodara.

News from the middle is that India have won the toss and they will bat. Thats two consecutive wins with the coin for Mahendra Singh Dhoni, and he had no hesitation to put his batsmen in. He did that at Chandigarh and India won a game. It remains to be seen what happens here at the IPCL ground.

I'm Jamie Alter, and along with George Binoy later in the morning will be your commentator for the day.

A crucial game, needless to day. If Australia win, there's no way they can lose the series. India need to prevent them doing that and make it 2-2 heading over to Nagpur.

Both sides have fielded unchanged sides.

There's less grass on this pitch than on the one in Chandigarh, and it looks a a batting paradise. That equates to runs, a good amount of them, and a tough day for the bowlers. A very flat pitch. (No hitting the high notes here!)

Incidentally, Sachin Tendulkar becomes the second player after Sri Lanka's Sanath Jayasuriya to feature in 400 ODIs. You can read a bit of what he had to say about "just another match" here.

And you can also read Anand Vasu's preview of this match.

We're not far away from the start. Do stay with us.

Let me quickly remind you about Slogout, the new online cricket game from Cricinfo. (Its one of my favorite past-times.) Play now!

8.50 am local Tendulkar received a trophy for completing 400 ODIs. There's a good crowd turned out.

Want to follow the game while at work, or just surfing the Net? Download Cricinfo's Desktop Alerts to get news, scores and wicket alerts from our website direct to your desktop. Click away - it's very easy...and free!

8.59 am local All ready for the start? I am, and so are the players. India's openers are out in the middle, having a chat with Ricky Ponting as a swarm of dragonflies buzz around them. And there's Rahul Dravid with the pads on sitting on the players' balcony.

Brett Lee has the new ball and will bowl to Sourav Ganguly, with two slips waiting. The umpires call play and off Lee goes!
